column5: Wind and rain have really done a number on the ice the last couple of days. Most lakes right in the Haliburton area are open now, or should be open by tomorrow. Just north of here it's going fast.
sweet...hoping to be up for ice out lakers!
thanks for the report! I'd like to get up there next week!  S.
North east part of Haliburton my cottage lake is still 80-90% iced over.  Smaller lakes and to the south are more open. Still 3 feet of snow in the bush where the sun cant get it.

Buddie came in today and said he was ouot walking on one of the lakes, Cant remember which one, might be a long time this spring. Ill find out which lake it was and edit this later.  It was Brady lake he was out on on sunday,, thought it would be 2 more weeks
anyone up this weekend who can give an update please?
